=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_HPZ2_ex2 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_bright mixed sound, with complex characteristics, featuring punchy attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with highpass character, and spectrally dense.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_bright
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: mixed
  spectral_complexity_mean: dense
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: highpass
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 0.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: 0.0000
  harmonic_regularity: 0.0000
  pitch_clarity: 0.0000
  inharmonicity: 0.0000
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: 34.7166
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: HPZ2 Example 2
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/HPZ2.html
// Tags: HPZ2, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 2 ---
// Compare:

{ WhiteNoise.ar(0.25) }.play;

{ HPZ2.ar(WhiteNoise.ar(0.25)) }.play;

// HPZ2 is useful to detect changes in a signal:
// see also HPZ1
(
{
    var changingSignal = LFNoise0.ar(1000);
    var hpz2 = HPZ2.ar(changingSignal);
    [hpz2, hpz2 > 0]
}.plot
);
